      "title": "Vocabulary — Units 7–12 (Sadlier Level F)",
      "content": "<h2>📖 Vocabulary Units 7–12 — Sadlier Level F</h2><p style=\"color:#666;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:16px\">120 words across 6 units. These appear as the first 20 questions on your AP Lang exam.</p><h3>Unit 7</h3><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:16px\"><thead><tr style=\"background:#e8eaf6\"><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Word</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Part of Speech</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>austere</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Severe or stern in manner; without adornment; plain; harsh or sour in flavor</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>beneficent</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Performing acts of kindness or charity; conferring benefits, doing good</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>cadaverous</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Pale, gaunt, resembling a corpse</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>concoct</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To prepare by combining ingredients; to devise, invent, fabricate</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>crass</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Coarse, unfeeling; stupid</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>debase</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To lower in character, quality, or value; to degrade, adulterate</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>desecrate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To commit sacrilege, treat irreverently; to contaminate, pollute</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>desist</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To cease doing something, forbear</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>disconcert</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To confuse; to disturb the composure of</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>grandiose</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Grand in an impressive or stately way; pompous, absurdly exaggerated</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>inconsequential</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Trifling, unimportant</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>infraction</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">A breaking of a law or obligation</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>mitigate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To make milder or softer; to moderate in force or intensity</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>pillage</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v./n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To rob by open force; plunder; (n.) act of looting; booty</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>prate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To talk a great deal in a foolish or aimless fashion</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>punctilious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Very careful and exact; attentive to fine points of etiquette or propriety</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>redoubtable</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Inspiring fear or awe; illustrious, eminent</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>reprove</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To find fault with, scold, rebuke</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>restitution</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Act of restoring to rightful owner; making good for loss or damage</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>stalwart</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj./n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Strong, sturdy, brave, resolute; (n.) a brave, strong supporter</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>stipend</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">A fixed sum paid periodically for services or to defray expenses</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>vulnerable</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Open to attack; capable of being wounded; unprotected</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Unit 8</h3><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:16px\"><thead><tr style=\"background:#e8eaf6\"><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Word</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Part of Speech</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>acrimonious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Stinging, bitter in temper or tone</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>bovine</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Resembling a cow or ox; sluggish, unresponsive</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>conducive</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Tending to promote or assist; helpful, favorable</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>consternation</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Dismay, confusion</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>corpulent</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Fat; having a large, bulky body</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>disavow</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To deny responsibility for or connection with</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>dispassionate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Impartial; calm, free from emotion</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>dissension</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Disagreement, sharp difference of opinion</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>dissipate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To cause to disappear; scatter; squander; be extravagant in pursuit of pleasure</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>élan</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Enthusiastic vigor and liveliness; a flair</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>expurgate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To remove objectionable passages from a written text; cleanse, purify</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>gauntlet</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Armored glove; challenge to combat; an ordeal</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>hypothetical</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Based on assumption or guess; provisional or tentative idea</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>ignoble</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Mean, low, base</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>impugn</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To call into question; attack as false</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>intemperate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Immoderate, lacking in self-control; inclement</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>perfidy</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Faithlessness, treachery</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>relegate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To place in a lower position; to assign or refer; to banish</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>squeamish</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Inclined to nausea; easily shocked; excessively fastidious or refined</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>subservient</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Subordinate in capacity; serving to promote some end; submissively obedient</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\"><strong>susceptible</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\">Open to; easily influenced; lacking in resistance</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Unit 9</h3><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:16px\"><thead><tr style=\"background:#e8eaf6\"><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Word</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Part of Speech</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>abate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To make less; to subside; to nullify; to deduct</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>adulation</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Praise or flattery that is excessive</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>anathema</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">An object of intense dislike; a curse or strong denunciation</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>astute</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Shrewd, crafty, showing practical wisdom</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>avarice</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">A greedy desire, particularly for wealth</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>culpable</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Deserving blame, worthy of condemnation</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>dilatory</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Tending to delay or procrastinate; not prompt; intended to postpone</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>egregious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Conspicuous, standing out (particularly in an unfavorable sense)</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>equivocate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To speak or act in a way allowing more than one interpretation; deliberately vague</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>evanescent</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Vanishing, soon passing away; light and airy</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>irresolute</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Unable to make up one's mind, hesitating</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>nebulous</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Cloudlike; cloudy in color; vague, confused, indistinct</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>novice</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">One who is just a beginner at an activity requiring skill and experience</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>penury</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Extreme poverty; barrenness, insufficiency</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>pretentious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Done for show; claiming merit or position unjustifiably; ambitious</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>recapitulate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To review a series of facts; to sum up</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>resuscitate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To revive, bring back to consciousness or existence</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>slovenly</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Untidy, dirty, careless</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>supposition</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Something assumed or taken for granted without conclusive evidence</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\"><strong>torpid</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\">Inactive, sluggish, dull</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Unit 10</h3><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:16px\"><thead><tr style=\"background:#e8eaf6\"><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Word</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Part of Speech</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>accrue</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To grow or accumulate over time; to happen as a natural result</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>annotation</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">A critical or explanatory note or comment, especially for a literary work</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>bedlam</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">A state or scene of uproar and confusion; pandemonium</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>covert</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj./n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Hidden, disguised, kept secret; (n.) a sheltered hiding place</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>debonair</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Pleasant, courteous, lighthearted; smooth and polished, urbane, suave</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>efficacious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Effective, producing results</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>equanimity</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Calmness, composure, refusal to panic</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>fortuitous</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Accidental, occurring by a happy chance; random</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>gratuitous</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Freely given; not called for by circumstances, unwarranted</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>imperious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Overbearing, arrogant; seeking to dominate; pressing, compelling</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>invective</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Strong denunciation or condemnation; abusive language</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>motley</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Showing great variety, heterogeneous, many colors</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>munificent</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Extremely generous, lavish</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>procrastinate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To delay, put off until later; stall</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>recondite</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Exceeding ordinary knowledge and understanding</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>reprobate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n./adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">A depraved, vicious, unprincipled person; (adj.) corrupt</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\"><strong>sedentary</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\">Characterized by continued sitting; remaining in one place; stationary</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Unit 11</h3><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:16px\"><thead><tr style=\"background:#e8eaf6\"><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Word</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Part of Speech</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>abstemious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Moderate, sparing (as in eating/drinking); characterized by self-discipline</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>censurable</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Deserving of blame or correction; reprehensible</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>contingent</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj./n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Possible but uncertain; dependent on; (n.) a representative group or detachment</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>corroborate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To confirm, make more certain, bolster, substantiate, verify</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>denizen</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">An inhabitant, resident; one who frequents a place</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>discursive</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Passing aimlessly from one subject to another; rambling, roving</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>disseminate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To scatter or spread widely; disperse, publicize, broadcast, circulate</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>dowdy</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Poorly dressed, shabby; lacking smartness or good taste; frumpy</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>florid</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Highly colored, reddish; excessively ornate, showy, flamboyant</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>foist</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To impose by fraud; pass off as genuine; bring about by stealth or coercion</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>gauche</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Awkward, lacking social graces, tactless, clumsy; uncouth</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>heresy</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">An opinion different from accepted belief; denial of something held sacred</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>inculcate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To impress on the mind by repetition; teach persistently and earnestly</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>palpable</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Capable of being touched or felt; easily seen, heard, or recognized</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>pernicious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Extremely harmful; deadly, fatal</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>salient</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Prominent, standing out, conspicuous</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>satiate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To satisfy completely; to fill to excess</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>sear</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To make dry or withered; to char or scorch; to harden or make unfeeling</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\"><strong>specious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\">Deceptive; apparently good or valid but lacking real merit</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Unit 12</h3><table style=\"width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:16px\"><thead><tr style=\"background:#e8eaf6\"><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Word</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Part of Speech</th><th style=\"padding:6px 10px;text-align:left\">Definition</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>absolve</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To clear from blame, responsibility, or guilt; acquit, exonerate, pardon</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>caricature</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n./v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Exaggeration of characteristic features; cartoon, parody; (v.) to lampoon</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>contiguous</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Side by side, touching; near, adjacent; adjoining, abutting</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>cupidity</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">An eager desire for something; greed, avarice</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>deleterious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Harmful, injurious, detrimental, pernicious, damaging</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>enthrall</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To captivate, charm, hold spellbound; to enslave; to imprison</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>extenuate</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">v.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">To lessen the seriousness of an offense by partial excuses; mitigate</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>implicit</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Implied or understood though unexpressed; unquestioning; potentially contained in</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>incisive</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Sharp, keen, penetrating, acute, perceptive</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>inimical</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Tending to cause harm; oppositional, adverse; unfriendly, hostile, antagonistic</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>ostentatious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Marked by conspicuous or pretentious display; showy, flashy, flamboyant</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>paragon</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">n.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">A model of excellence or perfection; exemplar, ideal example</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>prosaic</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Dull, lacking distinction; matter-of-fact; not poetic; commonplace, humdrum</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>redundant</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Extra, excess, more than needed; wordy, repetitive; superfluous, verbose</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>sanctimonious</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Making a show of virtue; hypocritically moralistic; self-righteous, holier-than-thou</td></tr><tr style=\"background:#fafafa\"><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\"><strong>scintillating</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;border-bottom:1px solid #eee\">Sparkling, twinkling; exceptionally brilliant; stimulating, lively, glittering</td></tr><tr><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\"><strong>winsome</strong></td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px;color:#666\">adj.</td><td style=\"padding:5px 10px\">Charming, attractive, pleasing, engaging, delightful</td></tr></tbody></table>",
